body:
Documents should explain basics of how to use the inspector properly.

Key topics:
* Linked widget and render object trees.
* How to select a widget on the device.
* Jumping to source location widgets were created at.

comment_data.body: @jacob314, is this covered by https://flutter.io/inspector/, or did we want more comprehensive docs?
We still need to add screenshots and text describing jumping to source location.
@jacob314, @Sfshaza indicated she's planning on working on the next iteration of these docs.

@Sfshaza, I'm going to move this out of the current milestone and into the 'On Deck' (pending) one. Please let us know how we can help here - providing notes / screenshots / ideas for what the docs should cover.

https://flutter.github.io/devtools/inspector
Now has up to date documentation.

milestone.description: Issues under consideration for upcoming milestones.
milestone.title: On Deck

title: Docs on inspector written on flutter.io (and / or existing docs updated)
